tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All results are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated creatinine (1.6 mg/dL), which may indicate reduced kidney function or dehydration. Glucose and HbA1c are normal, suggesting good glycemic control. Electrolytes and urea are within reference ranges. Recommend clinical correlation and, if not already known, further evaluation of renal function.
